En la secci√≥n de data del concurso de Kaggle, se presenta una breve descripci√≥n de cada una de las columnas del conjunto de datos.

TripType: a categorical id representing the type of shopping trip the customer made. This is the ground truth that you are predicting. TripType_999 is an ‚Äúother‚Äù category.

VisitNumber: an id corresponding to a single trip by a single customer

Weekday: the weekday of the trip

Upc: the UPC number of the product purchased

ScanCount: the number of the given item that was purchased. A negative value indicates a product return.

DepartmentDescription: a high-level description of the item‚Äôs department

FinelineNumber: a more refined category for each of the products, created by Walmart
